    "title": "Prince Pipes is Hiring: Quality Control Engineer (Senior)",
    "description": "Prince Pipes has an exciting opening for a Quality Control Engineer at our Mysuru office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Prince Pipes:\nPrince Pipes is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Oversee daily production operations to meet output targets\n• Train and supervise shop floor workers and supervisors\n• Manage supplier quality audits and vendor development\n• Ensure compliance with safety regulations and factory acts\n• Maintain accurate production records and prepare daily reports\n• Prepare production cost analysis and efficiency reports\n• Monitor equipment performance and coordinate preventive maintenance\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• CA / CMA / CFA certification\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Six Sigma\n• Proficiency in Lean Manufacturing\n• Proficiency in SAP MM/PP\n• Proficiency in SolidWorks\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain Management\n• Proficiency in 5S\n• Proficiency in PLC/SCADA\n• Proficiency in Quality Control\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Flexible working hours\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Referral bonus program\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Learning & development budget\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Mysuru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Prince Pipes!",
